<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="touch-v">touch <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /tʌtʃ/    美 /tʌtʃ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(伸手) 触摸；接触 (到)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t touch that dish — it’s very hot! 
别摸那个盘子，它烫极了!</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>As our glasses touched, he said, “Cheers!” 
我们碰杯，他说：“干杯！”</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her dress was so long that it was touching the ground. 
她的裙子太长，都拖地了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>触动；感动：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What he said really <strong>touched</strong> my <strong>heart</strong>. 
他的话确实触动了我的心弦。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-to-eat-drink-or-use-sth">3.<strong>[常与否定词连用] 吃；喝；用 to eat, drink or use sth：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You have hardly touched your food. 
你没怎么吃东西啊。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He hasn’t touched the money his aunt left him. 
他还没动过姑妈给他的钱。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>(说话或写作中) 简略提到；涉及：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The article touches many of the issues which are currently popular.
这篇文章涉及到了很多时下热门的话题。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="touch-down">touch down</h3>
<p>1.<strong>降落；着陆：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The plane finally touched down at the airport around midday. 
中午前后，飞机终于在机场降落。</p></div></div>